title: Woman killed by flying debris as Storm Doris batters UK
text:
Woman killed by flying debris as Storm Doris batters UK Last updated 07:05, February 24 2017 ANDREW YATES 
The sea whips up as Storm Doris blows into the English city of Blackpool. 
A woman has been killed by flying debris in central England as storm winds of more than 145kmh batter the United Kingdom. 
West Midlands Ambulance Service said the woman suffered serious head injuries in Wolverhampton, 225km northwest of London. 
Rain, snow and strong winds from a weather system dubbed Storm Doris closed roads on Friday morning (NZT), cancelled flights and for a time halted train travel to and from Euston Station, one of London's main terminals. â€” ITV News Central (@ITVCentral) February 23, 2017 
Heathrow Airport said about one in 10 flights was cancelled.
